      "writtenOn": "2021-01-12T19:42:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Per https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/jackc/pgx#Tx.Rollback, this will return ErrTxClosed when the transaction was successful (see e.g. the deferred call to rollbackAndLogError on line 40). So this function will produce an \"Error while rolling back\" warning even for successful transactions, which will probably be quite noisy. Should we only log said warning if the error type is not ErrTxClosed?\n\nIf so, I recommend renaming this \"rollbackAndLogIfError\" to make this a bit clearer.",
